   {:e #blake3 "60c04a4bc848efa769ffda950d8f3d1a259c23a51ae774486f5c093380c10996" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Comprehensive tests for all CAL tasks.\n\nUNIT TESTS (8 new):\n\n1. test_membership_strength_midpoint: membership_strength(0.5, 0.5, any_t) == 0.5\n2. test_membership_strength_monotonic: for sim1 > sim2, strength(sim1) > strength(sim2)\n3. test_membership_strength_bounds: for all inputs, result in [0.0, 1.0]\n4. test_membership_strength_temperature_sharpness: lower temperature -> sharper transition\n5. test_calibrate_threshold_insufficient_data: <5 observations returns None\n6. test_calibrate_threshold_bimodal: 10 observations in two clusters -> threshold between clusters\n7. test_calibrate_threshold_writes_policy_datom: after calibration, :policy/concept-join-threshold exists in store\n8. test_narrow_candidates_collapsed: mean jaccard > 0.8 -> FrontierKind::Narrow returned\n\nPROPERTY TESTS (2):\n9. proptest_membership_strength_in_unit_interval: for random sim, threshold, temperature, result in [0, 1]\n10. proptest_calibrate_monotonic: adding more observations to the same cluster doesn't move threshold toward that cluster\n\nE2E VERIFICATION:\n- scripts/e2e_calibrating_threshold.sh:\n  Fresh init, make 10 diverse observations, harvest, verify:\n  (a) :policy/concept-join-threshold datom exists with value != embedder default\n  (b) Concept distribution has entropy > 0 (not all in one concept)\n  (c) NOT all observations in all concepts (some have strength < 0.5)\n  (d) Frontier recommendation is not the generic 'what connects X to Y?' template\n\nDEPENDS-ON: CAL-2, CAL-3, CAL-4, CAL-5.\n\nFILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (tests) + scripts/e2e_calibrating_threshold.sh" :op :assert}
